    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>,<strong> chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>coriander stalks</strong> to a<strong> pestle & mortar</strong></p><p>Tip: Don't have a pestle & mortar? Use a food processor!</p><p>Add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and grind to a paste – this is your<strong> Thai-style paste</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and add your <strong>soy sauce</strong> – this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
